Kano State Government has confirmed 92 fresh cases of COVID-19, with 3 additional deaths in the state. This was confirmed by the state ministry of health in a tweet on Friday at exactly 11.25pm. It said with the fresh cases, the total infections is now 311. Kano State Ministry of Health Twitter handle reads, @KNSMOH,#COVID19KN Update as at 11:25pm 1st May 2020. 92 new cases of #COVID19KN cases confirmed. Total confirmed cases in @KanostateNg are now 311. 3 additional #COVID19KN deaths were recorded. Total #COVID19KN deaths are now 8. The Nation reports that the state recorded 3 additional deaths, hence total deaths recorded in Kano is now 8.